  "enhanced_information": "Steroids are indicated in certain forms of tuberculosis to manage inflammation and complications. In the case of meningitis, steroids are used to reduce inflammation and improve neurological outcomes. For pericarditis, steroids help decrease pericardial inflammation and lower the risk of cardiac complications. However, in ileo-caecal tuberculosis, steroids are generally contraindicated due to the risk of exacerbating the infection and worsening the disease. In adrenal involvement, steroids are indicated to address adrenal insufficiency and restore hormonal balance. Therefore, the correct answer is that steroids are not indicated in ileo-caecal tuberculosis."
